HEADWORD: Cubo-octahedron
<hw>Cu`bo-oc`ta*he"dron</hw> <pr>(-dr?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A combination of a cube and octahedron,
esp. one in which the octahedral faces meet at the middle of the cubic
edges.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

